<h2>LMS Support</h2>
Currently, Evernote-LTI only supports the <a href="https://canvas.instructure.com/">Canvas</a> learning management system.

<h2>Installation</h2>
Setting up an LTI tool is very simple!
<ol>
  <li>Open your Canvas course.</li>
  <li>Navigate to the Settings page from the sidebar.</li>
  <li>Go to the External Tools tab.</li>
  <li>Click "Add External Tool".</li>
  <li>Enter a tool name (this can be anything! we suggest "Evernote LTI"), a consumer key ("test" for now), and a consumer secret ("secret" for now).</li>
  <li>Change the Configuration Type to "By URL".</li>
  <li>Copy the toolconfig.xml URL and paste it into the "Configuration URL" field. Ours is: http://evernote-lti.herokuapp.com/tool_config.xml</li>
  <li>Click "Save Tool Settings", and you're done! You should see our editor button when editing anything now!</li>
</ol>